show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
Introducing the latest version of Channels!

- Membership
- Announcements
- Channel page customization
- Streamlined channel feeds

Watch the video to get a sense for the changes.

Rolling out over the next 30 minutes.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
Best way to think about the new direction for channels: text-based Twitter Space (or Clubhouse, /tavern, /farhouse, etc.)

- A bunch of people on stage that can talk
- Even more people in the audience listening
- If you're in the audience, you can raise your hand to speak, may get invited up, but unlikely, esp. if the audience is really large

but...with channel casts you can reply to any cast and the channel members / mods can discover it with a few clicks. So discoverability / chance of getting on stage is much better.

And remember: you can always cast in your home feed to your followers and create your own channel.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text: I‚Äôve got to admit the recent channel update has 1000x the UX of channels. I also think many including myself have a clearer vision on the role of channels and us as channel owners in onboarding people to Farcaster (dare I say crypto?). Bullish.

text:

text:
The difference in running a round on /base-builds pre and post update is night and day. I was spending about 5+ hours every weekend fighting spammers and low effort grifters. All that is gone. 

Incredibly happy with the update and excited to get rounds closer to a buttery smooth experience.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text: This is so helpful @pichi! As I was troubleshooting with @jacy we realized that if you don‚Äôt have priority mode turned on for notifications you‚Äôre not seeing the separate channel notifications which is super helpful so I recommend switching to priority mode so you get this ‚ÄúChannels‚Äù category.

cast.text:
Channel changes have been in effect for 48 hours and I have some lessons learned: 

1. Be sure to follow the channel you want to be invited to. Some automated tools don‚Äôt work correctly unless you already follow the channel. 

2. For hypersub gated channels, best to also follow @hyperbot until the kinks are worked out. 

3. Be sure your notifications are set to ‚ÄúPriority Notifications‚Äù so you can see the channel tab. Scroll the whole tab to make sure you didn‚Äôt miss an invite. 

4. There are a lot of bugs. Give grace and assume hosts have the best intentions but are trying to figure it all out too. 

5. I‚Äôm not longer getting notifications from anyone unless I follow them. This is supposedly a bug. For now, best to go through your casts and check the replies manually. You may have way more than you think. Also check ‚ÄúShow More Replies‚Äù often until more channels have more members.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
1. Personal channel -- your home feed. It comes with your Farcaster account. :)

2. There are 13K channels (at 2500 warps a pop). Arguably there are too many channels! 

3. If channels are really working in terms of building many thriving communities, then we can figure out if reducing price is the right lever. But channel cost isn't the limiting factor right now.

cast.text:
channels either need to become cheaper or users be more willing to add members and take a chance

idk why the high price other than mitigating spam but hopefully that does come down. everyone should have a personal channel at least

also I've seen some suggest a retroactive reward for users that were here before the changes..

gib warps or 1 free channel creation

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
1. Agree it‚Äôs hard for new users! But it‚Äôs always been hard for new users. We‚Äôre going to be adding ‚Äúonboard directly to a channel‚Äù when joining Farcaster as the next big project for channels.

2. Channels as hashtags / topics did not work. We iterated for a year trying to make it work.

3. So we‚Äôre trying a new direction that is more like public group chats with a feed UX.

4. A reminder that casting in your home feed like Twitter is available to everyone.

cast.text:
the new channels remove the little accessibility warp once had for the everyday user 
 
as a new user, i can no longer join warp & simply cast in any topic of my interest‚Ä¶

now, on top of paying the registration fee, i must also (in most cases) pay a monthly channel subscription‚Ä¶ 

no new users will deal with this; it was hard enough to get them past the $5 data fee 

the issues we‚Äôve had with ‚Äúcabals‚Äù & ‚Äúit‚Äù crowds are now 10x more divisive & exclusionary & immediately work against new users

on top of these channel subscriptions adding friction, they force you to pay (in many cases) the /owner/ of the channel via their hypersub

now this owner may or may not have any experience or expertise in the channels topic at hand

more likely than not, they were just the first ones to want to talk about it on warp - it‚Äôs just an interest‚Ä¶ so why make these people god?

it doesn‚Äôt matter if it‚Äôs a minimal cost, new users won‚Äôt pay 10-15 individual subscriptions to access channels of interest

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
Some unsolicited advice: Don‚Äôt think of the new channels framework as some new set of exclusive clubs. There is no benefit to joining a channel for the most part aside from posting privileges, so no point pining after memberships you may not even need. 

More helpful to consider the new system like a dynamic CAPTCHA where instead of frantically clicking on 15 fire hydrants, you just need to prove that you‚Äôre a human who will contribute quality content to a community. 

Attention is a very scarce resource, and no one owes it to you by default. Prove you‚Äôre not a spammer (and since most of you are not, it should be pretty easy) and then enjoy slop-free channels with the rest of us. 

Final note: if you are an earnest contributor looking for membership to a channel so you can continue to post there, give a little patience & grace to the owners / moderators for the next few days, as we all figure out the best tools to use for moderation. And don‚Äôt be afraid to send a friendly message asking to be invited.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
before you complain about not being allowed to cast in a channel:

write a short, simple, and thoughtful note to the owner or a moderator letting them know you‚Äôd like to contribute and see what they say

if this is too much for you then maybe it‚Äôs not that important and you can just post to main

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
when's the last time you made a major lifestyle change (diet, sleep, etc) and were 100% happy with it and adjusted after 2 days?

my guess is never. 

the new channel setup is a huge infrastructure change and <48 hrs old. allow it to settle. 

its new for all of us: merkle, users, mods. we'll figure it out together.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
Channel changes have significantly change the ¬´¬†FC game¬†¬ª we‚Äôre all playing.  Let‚Äôs talk abt it

Old meta: cast in channels for distribution 

New meta: cast in channels for connection

The reasons for casting in channels has changed. Casting in channels is friction - you have to select the channel rather than YOLOing your post to your followers.  The new changes add MORE friction (must be a member) while reducing algo boost.

We will likely have far fewer casts in channels but hopefully those casts will get engagement from people who actually care about the topic.  ‚ÄúConnection‚Äù isn‚Äôt easily measurable, but the idea is that you will more satisfied posting into a channel because the quality of discourse will be higher.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep165 Monday October 7, 2024 with guest cohost @heavygweit
text:
Product vs Distribution is a good high level frame, but you have to adjust it for your vertical. 

Anyone who has built social will tell you it‚Äôs not a great idea to focus on top of funnel until you have a good d30 retention, and bad retention is usually caused by things not working in the product. 

We have had solid d30 in the past, especially around frames launch but now it‚Äôs lower and we need to fix that first before worrying about top of funnel

cast.text:
Most of what I‚Äôve seen called ‚Äúgrowth‚Äù from dev day is really product and not at all about distribution 

i understand focusing on building a product that has clear differentiation/PMF but FC/WC disregards distribution   to an extent that‚Äôs pretty surprising for a social product
